HEADWORD: Glasseye
<hw>Glass"eye`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A fish of the great lakes; the wall-eyed
pike.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Far.)</fld> <def>A species of blindness in horses
in which the eye is bright and the pupil dilated; a sort of
amaurosis.</def> <rj><au>Youatt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glass-faced</ent>⟦br⟧
